 books, essays, interviews, and LP record album liner notes, it is essential reading for writers, historians, scholars, and music lovers of every stripe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Mai 2020) 0aPopular musicy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aGleason, Toby, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWenner, Jann08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2016z978311066771440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300221091423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300221091.jpg  a978-3-11-066771-4  YUP eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles